This paper proposes an abstract model for complex negotiation dialogue, which involves multiple agents interacting with each other. This falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) as it deals with the development of algorithms for intelligent agents. The paper also mentions the use of Reinforcement Learning, Stochastic Games, Transfer Learning, and One-Shot Learning, which are all subfields of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Game Theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper discusses Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) as it involves multiple agents interacting with each other. Finally, the paper mentions the benchmarking of optimisation algorithms, which falls under the category of Optimization and Control (cs.SI).
